= Mod Info

This modification's main premise is expanding content of base game in trivial way: Through granting the freedom of action to the player and automatizing processes in the game. This in theory should make it far easier to modify and adjust compared to the manual way of party popularity changes in base game or for that matter - in every other mod.

The secondary aspect of this modification is coverage of the unique events of the Weimar Republic era in Germany and giving them weight to influence the overall story, shaping it in even more unrecognizable ways than Dynamic does. For example, only the Zentrum mod (in development) cover events of Rural People's Movement and Green Front and there are even more events left uncovered by SPD-centric mods. 

In addition, the game brings modifiers, challenges and extensive sandbox content. It can be activated in the Library. 

However, the mod is pretty WIP (Work.In.Progress) and is highly experimental as new game mechanics are being tested. Not everyone will like it. Also, this game uses AI / LLM for complex codes (AND, temporarily, flavor text), so whether one is comfortable with this fact is up to the user.

Source Code: <a href="https://github.com/KesselFarben-Noncorp/social_democracy_horizon/tree/main">Click here</a>

Suggest your ideas and report the bugs, thanks!

Mod developers: GaufenSpelt / Visionary and Arkadyevna / Sonic Shapeshifter.

